  • NOTE: Single-pole application only. Neutral wire is required. Only works with 2.4 GHz Wi-Fi network. Package include: three separate switches with one 3-gang wall plate. The 3 gang wall plate is put in bottom of the packing box.
  • TOUCH CONTROL & LED BACKLIGHT: Tempered glass touch screen design,40ms high-speed touch-sensitive response. Blue indicator shows the on/off clearly, easy to find in darkness, but zero-impact on sleep. Low power consumption and long service life.
  • VOICE CONTROL: Smart switch compatible with Amazon Alexa，Google home assistant, just a simply voice command can let Alexa / Google Assistant turn on/off the light for you, free your hands and save time of walking around.
  • SET SCHEDULE & SCENE: Control your lights from anywhere. Secure control using the Smart Life App when you are home or away. Custom schedules and set times, let your lights function automatically. On at sunset, off at bedtime.Create scenes to control a group of lights.
  • GROUP CONTROL & DEVICE SHARING: Create a group in 'Smart Life' App, so you can trun on/off all the lights in the same group at the same time, And support control one device via many phones, you can share your smart switch to your family members.

  • CasSandra
    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    The best device I've ever bought (so far)
    Reviewed in the United States on October 2, 2020
    Style: Single Pole Smart Switch-3 Gang
    1.
    I purchased this to replace the original rocker switches and to eliminate the use of the limited SwitchMate device. SwitchMate is good but you can’t communicate with it outside of your home’s Wi-Fi network. So if I want to turn on the outdoor lights while away I... See more
    I purchased this to replace the original rocker switches and to eliminate the use of the limited SwitchMate device. SwitchMate is good but you can’t communicate with it outside of your home’s Wi-Fi network. So if I want to turn on the outdoor lights while away I couldn’t.

    I needed more control. I found this switch set.

    Do NOT get this unless you are a technician or can get a technician to do the install. This is not for the novice. The included instructions are not enough and the included wires are not of the needed size. I tried to install myself but after 2 days of trial and error I ended up calling an electrician, watching him I realized that it over my head. It required my tech to use additional wires on the ground and the neutral just to connect those, the line (power) was kept on the middle original switch and from there shared to the load on the 2 new switches. You really have to know what you’re doing it not as simple as, take that wire put it here, and take that wire and put it there.
    Wires had to be added to extend reach, good grade (20g) not the cheap ones in the box (DON’T USE THOSE).

    I had 2 days of frustration and he installed it in about 2 hours but even he had a time with the wires and getting everything squeezed into the junction box. I also found out that nothing in that particular box was grounded. A layperson would have never seen or rectified that. My future project now will be to check all the other switches in the house to make sure that they have a negative wire attached.

    Connecting to the existing SmartLife app was simple. Now I can control the outside lights at will. The best part of 2020.

    See pics (yes, I label everything - helps guests use the correct switch w/o having to guess). Used two in the front and one in the back.

    2 week update: still working great, absolutely no problems. They follow the schedule I made for them, turning on and off. Loving these switches.

    ***Anyone interested in my SwitchMate switches, find me on ebay "TechSis"👍🏽
    7 people found this helpful

  • Moani M.
    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Good reliable product
    Reviewed in the United States on March 26, 2021
    Style: Single Pole Smart Switch-2 Gang
    I have owned and installed 8 of these switches in my house. The first time I did it I had no electrical experience so I had to watch a bunch of YouTube videos to get a little understanding on how switches in general work. That being said with time and patience I figured it... See more
    I have owned and installed 8 of these switches in my house. The first time I did it I had no electrical experience so I had to watch a bunch of YouTube videos to get a little understanding on how switches in general work. That being said with time and patience I figured it out. Now if you are familiar with all this I would definitely say installation is quite simple. It comes with everything you need there are no functional design problems with this product. However it is bulkier than your regular non wifi switch so be prepared to make space for that by shortening wires. So everything fits in the box.
    Once that was done you just install the app and it will walk you through the install. The switches run off of 2.4ghz. Every router has two different options. 2.4ghz and 5ghz. Now if you have a router that displays both options in your list of wifi options. Just select the 2.4 the app will prompt you to use that. If you are like me and have an updater router that only has one option there is an option to switch pairing mode from EZ mode to AP mode. AP MODE will allow you to connect your phone to the devices wifi signal. The signal won't be strong so you may get a notification that say to switch to your regular wifi just select stay connected and as soon as you go back to the app it will start pairing.
    Like I said I have installed a bunch of these over time and paired them all with my Alexa devices.. These switches are an affordable price and they work just as well as the lutron. P.S I would not use them for fan switches use switches that are designated for fan use.. Hope this helps.
    6 people found this helpful

    Overall, this is a really good product. The installation was typical for any outlet, however, the pairing process was VERY simple!   • wrbrower
    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    I have made these work as 2-way and 3-way switches
    Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2018
    Style: Single Pole Smart Switch-2 Gang
    I have made these work as 2-way and 3-way switches. I am not going to go into detail on wiring, but if you can wire your existing boxes to get power to every switch location this will work. The last switch in the wiring series before the light fixture we will call... See more
    I have made these work as 2-way and 3-way switches. I am not going to go into detail on wiring, but if you can wire your existing boxes to get power to every switch location this will work. The last switch in the wiring series before the light fixture we will call "Hallway". In the other box(es) install the switches but only hook up the ground, the neutral and the line connection. Do not hook up the line out. The other boxes will essentially be 'remote controls' to run the "Hallway" switch. Get the switches working and controllable in the Smart Life (or Tuya) app.

    Now to make the system work:
    Create a scene where if you turn on Hallway light it turns on Remote 1 and Remote 2
    Create a scene where if you turn off Hallway light it turns off Remote 1 and Remote 2
    Create a scene where if you turn on Remote 1 it turns on Hallway and Remote 2
    Create a scene where if you turn off Remote 1 it turns off Hallway and Remote 2
    Create a scene where if you turn on Remote 2 it turns on Hallway and Remote 1
    Create a scene where if you turn off Remote 2 it turns off Hallway and Remote 1

    If you set it up right as you turn any switch on or off the other switch(es), whether they be the main switch or a remote switch, will become the same on or off state.
